    • Method Detail

      • evaluate

        public void evaluate(Individual individual,
            Log log)
        Description copied from class: Evaluator

        Evaluate the given Individuals. The Evaluator must call #setResult(EvaluationDescription, double) on individual.evaluationData for each evaluation type it defines in Evaluator.getEvaluationDescriptions().

        It is critical that this method is thread-safe (can handle multiple simultaneous calls).

        Specified by:
        evaluate in class Evaluator
        Parameters:
        individual - The Individual to evaluate.
        log - Whether, how and what details to log of the evaluation. How the log is interpreted and handled is up to the implementing class. If Log.NO_LOG is given then no logging is required.
